main today the \"gold standard\" in medical microbiology.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Robert_Koch_A_Life_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Robert_Koch#cite_note-Robert_Koch_A_Life-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> As a result of his groundbreaking research on tuberculosis, Koch received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physiology_or_Medicine\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine\">Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine<\/a> in 1905.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Robert_Koch_A_Life_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Robert_Koch#cite_note-Robert_Koch_A_Life-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Robert Koch","place_of_birth":"Clausthal , Prussia","place_of_death":"Baden-Baden , German Empire","text":"Robert Koch , Physiology or Medicine, 1905","year":1905.0}